"title": "2372: Jesus Christ, victory of",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "2372",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>Jesus Christ triumphs over and disarms all the powers of evil arrayed against him. Believers are able to share in this victory through faith in Jesus Christ.</p>\n<h2>The scope of Jesus Christ's victory</h2>\n<h3>Over temptation</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb4:15\">HEB 4:15</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt4:1-Matt4:11\">MAT 4:1–4:11</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke4:1-Luke4:13\">LUK 4:1–4:13</a></p>\n<h3>Over sin</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom5:20-Rom5:21\">ROM 5:20–5:21</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1John3:5\">1JN 3:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1John3:8\">1JN 3:8</a></p>\n<h3>Over Satan</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John12:31\">JHN 12:31</a></strong> <em>Satan is called “the prince of this world” in John's Gospel.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke10:18-Luke10:19\">LUK 10:18–10:19</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John14:30\">JHN 14:30</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John16:11\">JHN 16:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb2:14-Heb2:15\">HEB 2:14–2:15</a></p>\n<h3>Over evil spirits</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark1:23-Mark1:27\">MRK 1:23–1:27</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke4:33-Luke4:36\">LUK 4:33–4:36</a></p>\n<h3>Over all powers</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col2:15\">COL 2:15</a></strong> <em>“powers and authorities” include evil spiritual beings.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom8:38-Rom8:39\">ROM 8:38–8:39</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor15:24-1Cor15:25\">1CO 15:24–15:25</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph1:21-Eph1:22\">EPH 1:21–1:22</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph4:8\">EPH 4:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps68:18\">PSA 68:18</a></p>\n<h3>Over the world</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John16:33\">JHN 16:33</a></strong> <em>Here, as elsewhere in John's Gospel, “world” refers to the human race in rebellion against God.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Thess2:8\">2TH 2:8</a> <em>“the lawless one” represents the leader of human forces of evil</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1John5:4-1John5:5\">1JN 5:4–5:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev17:12-Rev17:14\">REV 17:12–17:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev19:11-Rev19:21\">REV 19:11–19:21</a></p>\n<h3>Over death</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom6:9\">ROM 6:9</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts2:24\">ACT 2:24</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor15:26\">1CO 15:26</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor15:54-1Cor15:57\">1CO 15:54–15:57</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Tim1:10\">2TI 1:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev1:18\">REV 1:18</a></p>\n<h2>The manner of Jesus Christ's victory</h2>\n<h3>By the written word of God</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt4:4-Matt4:10\">MAT 4:4–4:10</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke4:4-Luke4:12\">LUK 4:4–4:12</a></p>\n<h3>By his death on the cross</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb2:14\">HEB 2:14</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col2:15\">COL 2:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev12:11\">REV 12:11</a></p>\n<h3>By God's authority</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke11:20\">LUK 11:20</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt12:28\">MAT 12:28</a></p>\n<h3>By his spoken word</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt8:16\">MAT 8:16</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt8:8\">MAT 8:8</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke7:7\">LUK 7:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt8:13\">MAT 8:13</a></p>\n<h2>Consequences of Jesus Christ's victory</h2>\n<h3>Assurance for believers</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John16:33\">JHN 16:33</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Thess4:13\">1TH 4:13</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev5:5\">REV 5:5</a></p>\n<h3>Victory for believers</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor15:57\">1CO 15:57</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom7:21-Rom7:25\">ROM 7:21–7:25</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom8:37\">ROM 8:37</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom16:20\">ROM 16:20</a></p>",
